This paper deals with path planning algorithms for multiple robots in a mobile fulfillment system, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of state-of-the-art algorithms and simulation tools also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The monitoring of performance metrics such as throughput and path length indicates a possible interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
